00044 static void process_event_generic(const struct ast_event *event)
00045 {
00046    ast_log(LOG_DEBUG, "Event type: %u\n", ast_event_get_type(event));
00047 }
00048 
00049 static void process_event_mwi(const struct ast_event *event)
00050 {
00051    const char *mailbox;
00052    unsigned int new;
00053    unsigned int old;
00054 
00055    mailbox = ast_event_get_ie_str(event, AST_EVENT_IE_MAILBOX);
00056    new = ast_event_get_ie_uint(event, AST_EVENT_IE_NEWMSGS);
00057    old = ast_event_get_ie_uint(event, AST_EVENT_IE_OLDMSGS);
00058 
00059    ast_log(LOG_DEBUG, "MWI Event.  Mailbox: %s  New: %u  Old: %u\n",
00060       mailbox, new, old);
00061 }
00062 
00063 static void ast_event_process(const struct ast_event *event, void *userdata)
00064 {
00065    switch (ast_event_get_type(event)) {
00066    case AST_EVENT_MWI:
00067       process_event_mwi(event);
00068       break;
00069    default:
00070       process_event_generic(event);
00071    }
00072 }

00074 static char *event_gen(struct ast_cli_entry *e, int cmd, struct ast_cli_args *a)
00075 {
00076    struct ast_event *event;
00077    const char *mailbox = "1234@fakecontext";
00078    unsigned int new = 5;
00079    unsigned int old = 12;
00080    struct ast_event_sub *event_sub;
00081 
00082    switch (cmd) {
00083    case CLI_INIT:
00084       e->command = "event generate";
00085       e->usage =
00086          "Usage: event generate\n"
00087          "       Generate a test event.\n";
00088       return NULL;
00089 
00090    case CLI_GENERATE:
00091       return NULL;   /* no completion */
00092    }
00093    if (a->argc != e->args)
00094       return CLI_SHOWUSAGE;
00095 
00096    if (!(event_sub = ast_event_subscribe(AST_EVENT_ALL, ast_event_process, 
00097       NULL, AST_EVENT_IE_END))) {
00098       return CLI_FAILURE;
00099    }
00100 
00101    if (!(event = ast_event_new(AST_EVENT_MWI, 
00102          AST_EVENT_IE_MAILBOX, AST_EVENT_IE_PLTYPE_STR, mailbox,
00103          AST_EVENT_IE_NEWMSGS, AST_EVENT_IE_PLTYPE_UINT, new,
00104          AST_EVENT_IE_OLDMSGS, AST_EVENT_IE_PLTYPE_UINT, old,
00105          AST_EVENT_IE_END))) {
00106       return CLI_FAILURE;
00107    }
00108 
00109    ast_event_queue_and_cache(event,
00110       AST_EVENT_IE_MAILBOX, AST_EVENT_IE_PLTYPE_STR,
00111       AST_EVENT_IE_END);
00112 
00113    /* XXX This is a hack.  I should use a timed thread condition instead. */
00114    usleep(1000000);
00115 
00116    ast_event_unsubscribe(event_sub);
00117 
00118    return CLI_SUCCESS;
00119 }

00121 static char *event_get_cached(struct ast_cli_entry *e, int cmd, struct ast_cli_args *a)
00122 {
00123    struct ast_event *event;
00124    const char *mailbox = "1234@fakecontext";
00125 
00126    switch (cmd) {
00127    case CLI_INIT:
00128       e->command = "event get cached";
00129       e->usage =
00130          "Usage: event get cached\n"
00131          "       Test getting an event from the cache.\n";
00132       return NULL;
00133 
00134    case CLI_GENERATE:
00135       return NULL;   /* no completion */
00136    }
00137    if (a->argc != e->args)
00138       return CLI_SHOWUSAGE;
00139 
00140    event = ast_event_get_cached(AST_EVENT_MWI,
00141       AST_EVENT_IE_MAILBOX, AST_EVENT_IE_PLTYPE_STR, mailbox,
00142       AST_EVENT_IE_END);
00143 
00144    if (!event) {
00145       ast_cli(a->fd, "No event retrieved!\n");
00146       return CLI_FAILURE;
00147    }
00148 
00149    ast_cli(a->fd, "Got the event.  New: %u  Old: %u\n",
00150       ast_event_get_ie_uint(event, AST_EVENT_IE_NEWMSGS),
00151       ast_event_get_ie_uint(event, AST_EVENT_IE_OLDMSGS));
00152 
00153    ast_event_destroy(event);
00154 
00155    return CLI_SUCCESS;
00156 }
